<subSubSection pageId="462" pageNumber="463" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="462" pageNumber="463">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="462" pageNumber="463">
Northern Hemisphere, with about 215 species arrayed in four subtribes following Zamotajlov (2002): 
<taxonomicName genus="Deltomerina" lsidName="" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" rank="genus">Deltomerina</taxonomicName>
(about 115 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zamotajlov" authorityYear="2002" genus="Deltomerodina" lsidName="" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" rank="genus">Deltomerodina</taxonomicName>
(13 species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deuve" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Deltomerodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">Deltomerodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Deuve), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirkby" authorityYear="1837" genus="Patrobina" lsidName="" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" rank="genus">Patrobina</taxonomicName>
(about 80 species), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zamotajlov &amp; Lafer" authorityYear="2001" genus="Platidiolina" lsidName="" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" rank="genus">Platidiolina</taxonomicName>
(five species). The North American fauna is represented by 13 species (roughly 6.2 % of the world fauna).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="462" pageNumber="463" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="462" pageNumber="463">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="462" pageNumber="463">
Darlington (1938) and Lindroth (1961a) reviewed the North American species and provided keys for their identification. Subsequently to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lindrothâ€™s">Lindroth's</normalizedToken>
work, one species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Patrobus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septentrionis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">Patrobus septentrionis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was shown to consist of two distinct forms by Zamotajlov (2003c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
